caption: A taste of fresh cut deli sandwich 🥪 yummy
Great place for northeast style deli sandwich. One of the few restaurants that survive the pandemic. Great friendly staffs.

Helloooo!!! Well Ive got to tell my friends that my girl and I had a great breakfast here on our way to the airport...  Ready to fight back home after a few days in the city we decided to stop by reubens for a breackfast and found out that this deli has a extensive menu with soups, salads, charcuterie, cheeses, sandwiches, and a lot more.  My girl had a tuna salad, veggie soup, and latte. I had a chicken philly sandwich, and a cappuccino. Everything was very good.  My compatriot, the owner, treated us like home... He has owned the business for twenty five years, so I believe he knows something about...  Thanks a lot all of you there. We will see each other next time we are in town!!!
A good spot for a sandwich as well as a hot dog. Had the Chicago dog and it was tasty.
Very delicious.  Was craving pastrami and wanted something that taste close to Johnny's Pastrami in Los Angeles.  I have found a new place here in Atlanta.

I visit this place  a lot! This is my favorite spot to have a bite.  I go there many times. The cooking is excellent, the staff is courteous and the prices are affordable. I enjoy going in this restaurant for a decent supper.
If you are from New York. This is the spot

Ordered via Uber Eats... never been here before and did not realize prior to ordering that this is one of the top ten delis in the United States.  A Reuben is my go-to-sandwich, if I ever see on a menu, I have to try!  Figured it had to be good hear if it was in the name of the Restaurant!  I've lived in NJ/NY, OH, CA, and now Atlanta... I've also traveled to many places in the US, experiencing countless Reubens along the way.  This was one of the best I've ever had and it was delivered!  I can only imagine it being even better at the restaurant and look forward to my future visit in person!  The B&W Cookie was also dang good!!  This may be my new favorite place in Atlanta!  :P
Rude people. Pretty good food.
Awesome
Great Deli in Downtown Atlanta. I had the Reuben, it was delicious! It had sauerkraut and spicy mustard on rye. (Next time I will try the horse radish.) Reminded me of NYC.
Fantastic pastrami, plus the owners and all staff are great as well. Went back twice in 2 days.
The New Yorker on Rye is so freaking good and so is their Philly. I would say this is the best deli in Atlanta. The staff there is always really friendly, too. Highly recommend it!!!
Great service

Love Reubens and I am lucky I work closeby so I can come weekly!! They probably won't like me announcing to the Vegetarian World to 'EAT HERE ' since the employees are hilarious and low-key make fun of me every time i order.. but Reubens is a great veggie-lunch option! Their breads and toppings are sooo good (and fresh!). Ciabatta vegetarian sandwich is  the best sandwich i've ever had- there i said it. If you find yourself in downtown Atlanta, this place is legit!
I love REUBEN DELI, lunch date here every week!!!!!!
My favorite deli in the ATL!  The owner is a super cool guy as well.  Be ready to order!

Stupendous.
GREAT SANDWICHES. LOVED THE LIVERWORT.
Good sandwiches. Quick service.

Excellent place for delicious Cheap food. i like it here, great food & service. looking forward to coming back with my relatives. this place has a nice feel to it. atmosphere and food reminds me of virginia beach.
I wish I could come in here a lot more than I do but when I do come in here the food is amazing. I especially love the reubens here and the people and service are great.

If you haven't had Reuben's deli before, you're missing out. The sandwiches are always fantastic, the staff is incredibly friendly (even when joking around with you), and the service is on point. I highly recommend the Reuben sandwich for a new take on a classic, or the Jack Stack if you're looking to feed a small family.
Best sandwich I’ve ever had in Atlanta!
Hands down best deli in the ATL

He didn't even offer a pathetic apology, just began to argue with me about how the meat he was currently eating was hot??? I'm not sure how that had anything to do with me because my meal was COLD. This is the treatment I get for supporting a local business during a pandemic??? NEVER coming back again, and I urge others to do the same!

My husband ordered the Turkey Club, and I gotta say that you guys must know something. You are now my lil Coney Island here in Atlanta. Thanks

Came to Reubens,  looked on the menu that's on Google.  Get there order a Eastsider, now on the menu it's said it's $8 for the sandwich go to pay and it's a $13.04. When I informed him that's not what the provided menu states, and that's very misleading.  Instead of owner honor the online price or a  simple I'll look into,  he attacks me that its not his site that Google takes it upon themselves to make up prices and menu,😶🤔 wow what do you say to that. This is a run of the mill place, not clean or very nice inside, rude personnel  and the customer is always wrong. Good luck eating here.  BTW, THANKS FOR PROVING MY POINT.  Your very rude i actually feel sorry for your patrons.

Cheap food and the atmosphere at this location is great. Don't worry if it's busy, it is worth the wait. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.
Ok location for delicious cheap food. Cool place to meet and catch up with coworkers. Prices are appropriate for the quality.
My favorite spot for Cheap food. I like it here always quality food & service. The staff was very kind and attentive. Mood here is similar to Fresno's scene.
cheap food, so fresh. nice place to think about business. the service was friendly and observant. this place has a cool feel to it.
Cheap food, mmm, so fresh. I look forward to a return visit. The bill was reasonable I would say. Reminds me of a restaurant in Philadelphia that I enjoyed.
One of my preferred spots for quality cheap food. Came here on a Saturday. I had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here. It has an awesome atmosphere.
Cheap food... super satisfying. food was so tasty. i'll return with my coworkers.
The food is very good and the service is pushy and great. You have to try this place.

My first time eating here, always wanted to try deli style sandwiches. I had a roast beef and ham with cheese, sooooooooo good. I most definitely will be back. I will have to come on the weekend due too I work in Clayton County.
Terrific Reuben. If you like a little spice, ask for the homemade hot sauces spread. Phenomenal pepper flavor and kick.

I love a good corned beef sandwich and Reuben's doesn't disappoint. Having grown up outside of the-gasp-South, I experienced great corned beef in New York, New Jersey, Chicago and Detroit, the latter City hosted me during my High School years and had, in my humble opinion, the best corned beef on rye at a spot on the Northwest side-Lou's Deli. Well Reuben's has now joined my pantheon (can you say that about a sandwich rather than people) of great Deli's. My only complaint: they close waaay too early.
First time eating here fantastic, thank you
Love it
I love this spot! Closest ill ever get to NY in Atl lol
What a Sandwich
Hands down best sammiches in Atl

This is a great little restaurant. We went here from the State Capitol. It was a bit of a walk but not a problem. Parking is not easy downtown. We had 3 different sandwiches (all were fantastic, especially the Club). My Reuban was AMAZABELLES!! Reuban himself took our money and we also bought cookies (made daily by his daughter) and cheesecakes fresh from Carnegie Deli in NYC (soooooo goooood)!! We also got chilli and butternut squash soup (made fresh daily and also awesome). Prices are good for all that you get.

My opinion? This is the best deli in Atlanta.  But either way it has well-made sandwiches with top shelf ingredients at great prices and extensive choices. Used to work downtown and frequented it several times a week, live further out now, but they are on ubereats for delivery!
Beat sandwiches in town!!!

Amazing experience. True New York style to just yell out an order, they are interactive and fun. The sandwiches are of the highest quality. Prices are fair for how large the sandwiches are. I got the classic and could only finish half of it. Don’t forget to yell the type of bread and sauce you want. I will be back any time I’m in Atlanta. They do close at 4pm so make sure to get there for lunch, it’s worth a bit of a walk if your hotel is further.
This is got to be the most incredible cornbeef i've ever had in my life
Really good sandwich. Very generous with meat and had an option for gluten free bread. Gluten free bread was abit on the soft side to hold as a sandwich but still really good! Highly recommend.

I was happy to find this sweet jewel in Downtown Atlanta. Being a New Yorker who is totally homesick  The double meat corn beef Reuben with everything on it was the bomb and the pastrami on rye with mustard remind me of Carnegie Deli from back in the days! And yes yes yes I finally found knishes! I would of gave 5 stars but the knishes was not warm crispy and steamy like we like them in New York and it took too damn long to get them! I’ll be back for sure to enjoy the nice spot in Atlanta that remind me of my hometown NYC 🥰🥃
The real deal deli!
Some of the best cheese eggs and rye toast I've ever had in GA. Affordable, friendly, good on a rainy day, or any other day I would wager.

Great New yorker hot sandwich. Worth every penny. Great customer service and very friendly and approachable. Makes you feel comfortable. Any minor issues,  i.e sticky table, they wiped it down immediately. Would eat here everyday because they have a great variety of hot and cold dishes including breakfast. Different sandwich for everyday of the week.
Great deli, great food. The sandwiches are really hearty, they don't let you go hungry
Authentic NY deli. Fantastic corned beef and pastrami. Definitely worth a visit.
Great Ruben and atmosphere, will be back
Rude staff
Now this is truly a hidden GEM! The MEAT on any sandwiches is pure GOLD! You got to go and get a sandwich from there. Haven't eaten thier breakfast yet! To be continued...
Down to earth old school atmospere. You can really taste what a difference quality ingredients make. Only place I have seen a 2x egg omelet. For me 3x eggs is too much.
Authentic NY deli. Awesome food.
I would of posted a picture but I couldn't stop eating. BEST SANDWICHES DOWNTOWN!!!!

I am so glad I walked in instead of ordering online. This was my first time and the guys (B & Omari) who helped me were just awesome. They were so genuine and friendly. (I planned to take a pic but it's all gone. Just know it was super amazing!!!)

Eastsider was killer. Best corned beef/pastrami I’ve ever had. The only corned beef nearly as good is the one Zingerman’s  makes in Ann Arbor, Mi ( and they are $20 a pop there). Great atmosphere, great selection - one hell of a deli. I’ll be back a lot

One of the best deli's in Atlanta, in my opinion.  New York tendencies and delicious selections. Located in GSU campus on Luckie Street.  Try the Jack Stack

Good Service and pretty reasonable prices.  Godfather was pretty good.  Adequate amount of meat to bread ratio. Not the best ive ever had but i would absolutely order it again! Solid bread and veggies.  Lil dissatisfying the hot peppers they had were diced jalapenos peppers.  But overall solid.  The hot corned beef was not great.  They do not make their pastrami or corned beef at ruebens.  Real DELICATESSEN's usually make at least one of the two of these, sometimes even make their own turkey.  Theirs  was THUMANNS. (Claimed it was doctored)  It was not bad at all(thin cut which i love) but you CAN NOT claim to be a top 10 deli and not make some of your cold cuts in house.  That is really ridiculous statement that would only fly in the south. The rye bread was terrible.  Fell apart. Wasnt really a rye.  I actually threw out the most of the bread.  I did not try the pastrami bc it was boarshead.  Boarshead pastrami is what people who have never had really good pastrami THINK is good pastrami.  KAUFFMAMS DELI IN EVANSTON/SKOKIE if you wanna go to real deli. MINDBLOWING
Best sandwich in town. New York style deli. Come here for great food. Know your order before you step up!!
Great food

Just like back home NJ food is great my new favorite place and the people that own and operate the place are very friendly 👍👍so if u looking for good food n friendly people this is the place

You have to eat here! Authentic deli sandwiches, quaint seating and an amazing staff and manager! I can't tell you how wonderful the whole experience really is, you simply have to try it. The sandwiches are delicious, the cookies homemade, I'm getting hungry just thinking about it. You owe it to yourself to add this to your list of regular eats!

My first time here and I was extremely pleased. This is a counter service New York style deli. Call out your order and what toppings you want. I had the "New Yorker", corned beef and pastrami on extremely fresh rye bread with good spicy mustard. The sandwich was one of the best I've had in years. There is nothing fancy about this place at all. In addition to a wide choice of sandwiches, they have soups and salads, good sides, coffee drinks and desserts. I will definitely be back and if you are in the neighborhood and looking for a really good quick meal, I definitely recommend this place.

Best Pastrami sandwich in Georgia. I have no desire to go back to NJ anymore. Reuben's is for real with NY deli style sandwiches!

Amazing reuben. The bread was even delicious. Tastes freshly made, perfect temperature, and the sauerkraut is equally amazing. Best sandwich near the Peachtree Center and worth the walk.

Great spot. Hard working employees who enjoy the product they put out.  The meats are amazing, but the bread is just ok.  The birch beer on tap is great addition as well.

Most people know Reuben's as being a New York style sandwich shop, but they also have an Amazing Breakfast Menu!!! You can get 2,3,or 4 egg omelets, the largest and fluffiest pancakes you have ever seen and a wonderful big breakfast combo meal featuring pancakes, eggs, bacon or turkey sausage all hot and fresh off the grill. You can also add any of their wonderfully carved/shaved lunch meats to your omelet as well. So if you're hungry by 8:00 in the morning and you want a real good breakfast that might even make you skip lunch, head on over to Reuben's and enjoy a treat!!! Natalie

Very generous portions. Great fresh food. Reminds me of delis in Chicago. Corned/pastrami sandwich was very delicious. I will definitely be back.

This is the ABSOLUTE BEST deli I've ever visited in my life!! I will make it a point to stop through anytime I'm in or passing through Atlanta. I don't know which one is better, the food or customer service!! If I could've given 10 stars I would!!

Part of a big event that concluded at the CNN center and, hot and famished, stumbled into this place on our way back to a less crowded MARTA station. Awsome!!

NY Style deli with the attitude and quality! Be ready to order, wait for them to customize your sandwich when asked, and enjoy the direct friendly service. My go to here is the Turkey Reuben. I think they use all Boars Head deli meats, so it's good stuff!
Just the Best

New York style sandwiches which are probably hands down the best in Atlanta! The staff is always awesome and amazing every time I go! The owner is very personable and he takes the time to greet each and every customer. I am usually in and out (for to go orders) in and approximately 5 minutes during peak hours. If you are in the area I highly recommend you take the time to drop in and check them out!
A favorite spot for tasty cheap food. food was so yummy. the staff was helpful and kind. prices are appropriate.

Great food. Reminds of home in NYC

Great meaty sandwiches. Worth it man. Come hungry.

Amazing sandwiches. Been looking for some good sandwich places down here that are comparable to Jersey delis. This is definitely top of the list.

Been coming here since my sophomore year in college at GSU. Hands down the best sandwiches in Atl. Reminds of of going to the deli back home, we Northerners grew up on deli sandwiches. Tuna

You can see the slicer working as you line up to order. Everything is made to order. They also carry Zapp's chips. That's a nice Southern touch for a real NY-style deli. I'd put this deli up against any NYC deli.
Full.
Best deli in all of Atlanta. Don't let the lack of free parking stop you from going! Closest thing ATL has to an NY deli.

I had my taste for a Reuben Sandwich & I was told to go here . Great sandwiches.

I ordered the New Yorker Reuben.... it was by far one of the best sandwiches I've had in years! The atmosphere definitely has a Northeastern feel to it. I will definitely be back whenever I stop in Atlanta!
Best sandwiches ever.  Get the reuben with pastrami, thousand island dressing, and spicy mustard. It will change your life.
GREAT sandwiches and a fun atmosphere. If you’re in the area and hungry, it’s a must.

For homesick Northerners from the Tri-State area, you'll feel at home from the moment you walk in. Staff is on point and moves those orders out just like the delis back home. Craving a real Reuben, a dill pickle or a potato knish like the ones you bought from the street cart vendors? Hit this place up, it's what you've been looking for in Atlanta. Finish up your meal with a slice of cheesecake doing a bit of people watching the wonderful humans and catching the vibe of Broad Street or just enjoy the staff's friendly banter between themselves or with customers. Highly recommend.

Absolutely delicious. It's difficult to find a good sandwich shop, but doubly difficult finding a good place in an unfamiliar city. The staff are really nice and make great recommendations. Will be back anytime we are in the area!
After I ate here a few years ago I became in love. The cleanliness & quality of food is always amazing.
Fantastic staff, amazing food. Do not be shy. If you want something, ask for it. Also ask staff for recommendations coz they are fantastic.

Came here off a reference and i couldn’t be any happier with the quality of the food. I ordered the pastrami Reuben and it was melt in your mouth delicious! First bite i savored for quite some time. This place is awesome. The food is delicious a the customer service top notch. I joked and chopped it up with the owner for 20 minutes like we knew each other for years. Outstanding! Great service. Delicious food. Excellent coffee. I loved the vibe - everyone's loud with lots of energy, laughing and carrying on. They instantly make you feel like you're part of the family - like you've been coming there for years. Fantastic place. Can't wait to go back.
